President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2015 as Jewish American Heritage Month in the United States. He acknowledges the significant contributions Jewish Americans have made to the country and emphasizes the importance of standing up for religious freedom and combating anti-Semitism. The proclamation also highlights the 70th anniversary of the liberation of Dachau and recognizes the ongoing struggles faced by Jewish communities around the world. President Obama reaffirms America's commitment to the security of the State of Israel and the close bonds between the two nations. The proclamation encourages Americans to learn more about Jewish heritage and observe the month with appropriate programs and activities.